extendedInfo.description: If bug exists, please tell us (E-mail), we will fix it as soon as possible.The Lord of the Rings is a high fantasy epic written by philologist and University of Oxford professor J. R. R. Tolkien. The story began as a sequel to Tolkienâs earlier, less complex childrenâs fantasy novel The Hobbit (1937), but eventually developed into a much larger work. It was written in stages between 1937 and 1949, much of it during the Second World War. It is the second best-selling novel ever written with over 150 million copies sold.The films were directed by Peter Jackson and distributed by New Line Cinema. Considered to be one of the biggest and most ambitious movie projects ever undertaken, with an overall budget of $285 million, the entire project took eight years, with the filming for all three films done simultaneously and entirely in Jacksonâs native New Zealand.Theme consists of many wallpapers and many icons for popular application and graphic user interfaces for different devices(HTC, Samsung, Motorola, etc). You can change the Wallpapers from the menu by selecting âChoose Wallpaperâ. The first five Wallpapers are stored in the application. Everyone else will be downloaded from the Internet and stored in a folder(wallpaper _duomob).This theme is compatible with Crazy Home Pro, Crazy Home Lite, ADW Launcher, Live Home, Open Home, Open Home 6, aHome, 91 Panda Home, 91 Panda Home 2.If using Crazy Home, once it is installed and running, press your Menu Key -> Crazy Menu -> Appearance -> Set Theme.If using ADW.Launcher, once it is installed and running, press your Menu Key -> More -> ADWSettings -> Themes Preferences.If using Go Launcher Ex, once it is installed and running, press your Menu Key -> Themes-> Select theme-> Apply.This application does not violate the copyright and does not claim to it.All that is in this appendix are collected from free sources.If you are the author of the material or the copyright holder for it and against its use in this, please contact me and the material will be removed or will be listed your copyright.
